CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1956, pg. A2 reads: "Exhibit at Library - A collection of wood carvings, done by Atty. K. Leroy Irvis, is on exhibition at the Carnegie Library on Wylie Ave: The collection includes African heads, a series of dogs, and museum pieces carved of ebony and cherry wood.  Already on view for the past two weeks, the collection will remain at the library for at least another ten days. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Display of sculptures by K. Leroy Irvis, in interior of the Carnegie Library of Pittsburgh, Hill District
